> I am (OK, Tom Tarka is) trying to get my 1973 bus running.  This bus has a
> 1978 FI system installed, and should be thought of as a '78 for diagnostic
> purposes.  The symptoms and diagnostic we have followed  are as follows:
> 
> Dwell and timing are good, coil is producing spark.
> All vacuum lines are connected
> 
> NB: the double relay is  defective, and the gas pump runs whenever the
> ignition is on
> when the ignition is turned on, gasoline pressure rises *slowly* to 40psi
> (about 5 seconds)
> when cranked after a 1-2 minute rest period, the engine will fire up for a
> second or two, then die.
> further attempts at starting do nothing until the bus has rested for a
> minute or two.
> 
> Anyone have any suggestions?  We replaced the fuel filter without affecting
> the slow rise in fuel pressure, we have a goodused gas pump courtesy of
> Barry Burneskis and installing that is the next step, but it's time to ask
> the list for ideas.  Got any?
> 
> TIA,
